10. Broader Impact

This research contributes to:

Safer genome editing therapies

AI-assisted scientific discovery

Democratization of computational biology tools

Development of reproducible AI-science pipelines


The long-term vision is the establishment of reliable AI systems capable of assisting in high-stakes scientific research, bridging computational modeling and biological experimentation.


---

11. Conclusion

Genome editing through CRISPR has made DNA programmable, yet repair remains probabilistic.
Large language models demonstrate reasoning capacity but lack scientific reliability.

This proposal integrates sequence modeling, retrieval-grounded reasoning, and multi-LLM orchestration to construct a scientifically rigorous AI-assisted CRISPR modeling framework.

If successful, this work will advance both computational genomics and AI-assisted scientific methodology.


